{"id": 8002, "source": "pestle", "subject": "chemistry", "course": null, "level": "SL", "paper": "1", "year": "2020", "session": "20N", "subtopic": "11-3-spectroscopic-identification-of-organic-compounds", "title": "20N.1.SL.TZ0.29", "topic_id": "11", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">What is the index of hydrogen deficiency (IHD) in cyclohexanol?</span></p>\n<p><img height=\"101\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" style=\"display: block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" width=\"65\"/></p>\n<p>A.  <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p>B.  <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math></p>\n<p>C.  <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math></p>\n<p>D.  <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math></p>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>B</p>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>Slightly more than half of candidates could deduce an index of hydrogen deficiency. It was a poor discriminating question with distractors being chosen equally. </p>\n</div>"}